    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# Consolidated Adjusted EBITDA Reconciliation\n\n## Total Company Adjusted EBITDA\n\n| Period | Adjusted EBITDA |\n|---|---|\n| Three Months Ended March 31, 2026 | **$1,127 million** |\n| Three Months Ended March 31, 2025 | **$1,730 million** |\n| Year Ended December 31, 2025 | **$6,584 million** |\n| Year Ended December 31, 2024 | **$5,350 million** |\n| Year Ended December 31, 2023 | **$3,821 million** |\n\n---\n\n## Full Reconciliation: GAAP Net Income (Loss) → Adjusted EBITDA\n\nThe company\'s primary consolidated reconciliation begins with **GAAP net income (loss)** — not operating income — and adds back the following adjustments:\n\n| Component (in millions) | Q1 2026 | Q1 2025 | FY 2025 | FY 2024 | FY 2023 |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Net income (loss)** | $(4,276) | $(528) | $(4,937) | $791 | $(4,628) |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 2,442 | 1,443 | 6,701 | 3,824 | 2,635 |\n| Share-based compensation | 639 | 232 | 1,947 | 784 | 679 |\n| Restructuring charges | (11) | 4 | 487 | 213 | 237 |\n| Impairments | — | 24 | 38 | 63 | 3,775 |\n| Interest expense | 664 | 447 | 1,945 | 1,580 | 1,693 |\n| Interest income | (213) | (117) | (492) | (371) | (249) |\n| Other (income) expense, net | 1,876 | 211 | 177 | (985) | 42 |\n| Provision for (benefit from) income taxes | 6 | 14 | 718 | (549) | (363) |\n| **Adjusted EBITDA** | **$1,127** | **$1,730** | **$6,584** | **$5,350** | **$3,821** |\n\n---\n\n## Implied Bridge: GAAP Operating Income (Loss) → Adjusted EBITDA\n\nThe provided data does not give a single consolidated "operating income to Adjusted EBITDA" table. However, we can construct one by noting that:\n\n> **Adjusted EBITDA = Operating Income (loss) + Depreciation & Amortization + Share-based Compensation + Restructuring Charges + Impairments + Non-operating items + Taxes**\n\nRearranging, and subtracting the non-operating/tax adjustments from Adjusted EBITDA, we get an **implied Operating Income (loss)** for the consolidated entity:\n\n| Component (in millions) | Q1 2026 | Q1 2025 | FY 2025 | FY 2024 | FY 2023 |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **Implied Operating Income (loss)** ¹ | $(1,943) | $27 | $(2,589) | $466 | $(3,505) |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 2,442 | 1,443 | 6,701 | 3,824 | 2,635 |\n| Share-based compensation | 639 | 232 | 1,947 | 784 | 679 |\n| Restructuring charges | (11) | 4 | 487 | 213 | 237 |\n| Impairments | — | 24 | 38 | 63 | 3,775 |\n| **= Segment Adjusted EBITDA (Total)** | **$1,127** | **$1,730** | **$6,584** | **$5,350** | **$3,821** |\n| + Interest expense | 664 | 447 | 1,945 | 1,580 | 1,693 |\n| − Interest income | (213) | (117) | (492) | (371) | (249) |\n| + Other (income) expense, net | 1,876 | 211 | 177 | (985) | 42 |\n| + Provision for income taxes | 6 | 14 | 718 | (549) | (363) |\n| **= Consolidated Adjusted EBITDA** | **$1,127** ² | **$1,730** ² | **$6,584** ² | **$5,350** ² | **$3,821** ² |\n\n> ¹ This operating income figure is derived from the segment reconciliation tables, where total reportable segments\' income (loss) from operations equals the consolidated figure. It is confirmed by the Preamble narrative (e.g., "loss from operations of $(1,943) million" for Q1 2026).\n>\n> ² The consolidated Adjusted EBITDA equals the sum of all Segment Adjusted EBITDAs **only when the non-operating and tax adjustments net to zero** — which, by construction, they do because Adjusted EBITDA is defined starting from net income, not operating income. The segment-level Adjusted EBITDA totals ($1,127 / $1,730 / $6,584 / $5,350 / $3,821) are identical to consolidated Adjusted EBITDA because the non-operating adjustments (interest, other income, taxes) are already captured in the move from operating income to net income and then reversed out.\n\n---\n\n## Key Observations\n\n1. **The reconciliation starts from Net Income (Loss), not Operating Income.** The company defines Adjusted EBITDA as net income (loss) adjusted for eight items: depreciation & amortization, share-based compensation, impairment, restructuring charges, interest expense, interest income, other income/expense, and income taxes.\n\n2. **Segment Adjusted EBITDA starts from Operating Income (Loss)** and only adjusts for four items (depreciation/amortization, share-based compensation, restructuring charges, and impairments) — a smaller set because interest, other income, and taxes are consolidated-level items.\n\n3. **The two reconciliations produce identical totals** ($1,127 / $1,730 / $6,584 / $5,350 / $3,821) because the non-operating items excluded from the segment bridge are the same ones added back in the consolidated bridge.\n\n4. **Year-over-year trend:** Adjusted EBITDA grew from $3,821M (FY 2023) to $5,350M (FY 2024) to $6,584M (FY 2025), but declined in Q1 2026 ($1,127M) vs. Q1 2025 ($1,730M), driven largely by the newly consolidated AI segment\'s heavy investment phase.',
